00:00:07.760 --> 00:00:11.490
which allowed them to stand up to shoot their
bows and arrows.

00:00:11.490 --> 00:00:17.090
Nobility in Western Europe adopted the style
as a symbol of machismo, and the higher the

00:00:17.090 --> 00:00:22.400
heels you wore, the wealthier you appeared
because they were so impractical for walking

00:00:22.400 --> 00:00:24.029
on cobbled streets.

00:00:24.029 --> 00:00:30.570
In the 1670s, the diminutive King Louis XIV
loved how high heels made him taller, and

00:00:30.570 --> 00:00:36.610
he ordered that only members of his court
could don his trademark red heels.&nbsp;

00:00:36.610 --> 00:00:42.829
Women began to adopt masculine fashion, including
the high heel, but by the 1740s men’s fashion

00:00:42.829 --> 00:00:48.540
became more practical and less ostentatious
and high heels were considered foolish.

00:00:48.540 --> 00:00:54.940
It wasn’t until the mid-19th century that
high heels on women symbolized female sexuality,

00:00:54.940 --> 00:00:59.170
largely due to their use in pornographic postcards.

