their jackets, or to distinguish themselves

00:01:28.020 --> 00:01:29.950
from other soldiers.

00:01:29.950 --> 00:01:35.100
During the Thirty Years War in the early 1600s,
Croatian mercenaries were hired by France's

00:01:35.100 --> 00:01:40.730
King Louis XIII, and Parisians loved their
colorful knotted neckerchiefs - with the word

00:01:40.730 --> 00:01:45.310
cravat coming from a corrupt French pronunciation
of Croate.&nbsp;

00:01:45.310 --> 00:01:50.860
